HEADWORD: familial
<hw>familial</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>relating to or having
the characteristics of a family; <as>as, children of the same
<ex>familial</ex> background; <ex>familial</ex>
aggregation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>tending to occur among members of a family, usually
by hereditary transmission; <as><ex>familial</ex> traits</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genetic, hereditary, inherited, transmitted,
transmissible.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Familiar</ent>⟦br⟧
